Dice Game

Description:
-------------
This is a simple two-player dice game built with HTML, CSS, and JavaScript.
Players click the "Roll Dice" button, and two dice images are rolled randomly.
The player with the higher number wins. If both dice show the same number, it's a draw.

Features:
---------
- Random dice roll for Player 1 and Player 2
- Dynamic display of winner or draw
- Beginner-friendly JavaScript using DOM manipulation

How to Play:
------------
1. Open dice.html in a web browser.
2. Click the "Roll Dice" button.
3. Dice images will update with random numbers.
4. The winner will be displayed above the button.

Folder Structure:
-----------------
Dice-Game/
│
├─ dice.html      --> Main HTML file
├─ dice.css       --> CSS file for styling
├─ dice.js       --> JavaScript file for dice logic
└─ Images/         --> Folder containing dice1.png to dice6.png

